# --- Intro
lifeaquatic.manuals.almanac.chapters.introduction.title=Introduction
lifeaquatic.manuals.almanac.chapters.introduction.page0=Greetings, undersea explorer!<br><br>The book you have in your hand contains all the knowledge I have collected during my travels through §1the deep§8.<br><br>While I have traveled far, the ocean is vast and I do not pretend to have seen it all.
lifeaquatic.manuals.almanac.chapters.introduction.page1=The seas contain many varied treasures and wonders to discover! What I have catalogued here is but a meagre sampling of what the deep hides.<br><br>I pray you will add to this chronicle with the discoveries you make on your travels.<br><br>Sincerely,<br>Steve

# --- Ores
lifeaquatic.manuals.almanac.chapters.ores.title=Ores and Resources
lifeaquatic.manuals.almanac.chapters.ores.page0=Exploration of the sea requires specialized equipment to protect the human body from the extreme conditions.<br><br>Simple iron is insufficient-- we must use other, more robust materials instead.
lifeaquatic.manuals.almanac.chapters.ores.page1=§6Copper Ore§8 is found in the world between layers 38 and 48, and requires a Stone Pickaxe to harvest.<br><br>The ore will smelt into copper ingots which are used in crafting basic machines and gear, as well as in alloying.
lifeaquatic.manuals.almanac.chapters.ores.page2=§3Tin Ore§8 is found in the world between layers 18 and 28, and requires a Stone Pickaxe to harvest.<br><br>The ore will smelt into tin ingots which are used in crafting basic machines and gear, as well as in alloying.
lifeaquatic.manuals.almanac.chapters.ores.page3=§0Nickel Ore§8 is found in the world between layers 33 and 43, and requires an Iron Pickaxe to harvest.<br><br>The ore will smelt into nickel ingots.<br><br>Nickel is exceptionally resistant to corrosion and is thus well-suited for use in aquatic equipment.

